WEBVTT

00:00:02.780 --> 00:00:04.977
There's always the custom that when a person

00:00:04.977 --> 00:00:07.536
is about to die, they first make a wish and then

00:00:07.536 --> 00:00:08.360
they bury them.

00:00:09.940 --> 00:00:12.473
There was a person who used a wheelchair

00:00:12.473 --> 00:00:14.816
and when he was about to die,

00:00:14.816 --> 00:00:18.140
with all his family around his bed, he made his wish.

00:00:18.120 --> 00:00:21.320
When I die, I want them to put it inside the coffin.

00:00:23.760 --> 00:00:25.720
And the family granted his wish.

00:00:25.820 --> 00:00:27.669
The day of the funeral arrived,

00:00:27.669 --> 00:00:30.466
and the family buried him with his wheelchair.

00:00:31.420 --> 00:00:32.840
The second person was blind,

00:00:32.840 --> 00:00:34.600
and when he was about to die,

00:00:34.600 --> 00:00:37.100
with all his family around his bed, he made his wish.

00:00:37.100 --> 00:00:40.420
I want that when I die, please, and the family granted it.

00:00:40.420 --> 00:00:44.111
When he died, at the funeral they buried the blind person

00:00:44.111 --> 00:00:46.326
and placed his cane inside the coffin.

00:00:47.620 --> 00:00:49.817
And the third was an oral deaf person

00:00:49.817 --> 00:00:52.596
and when he was about to die with all his family

00:00:52.596 --> 00:00:53.700
he made his wish.

00:00:53.700 --> 00:00:55.600
I wish, and his family granted it.

00:00:55.600 --> 00:00:58.207
When they buried him, they put the cochlear implant

00:00:58.207 --> 00:00:59.983
and the hearing aid inside the coffin.

01:01:01.340 --> 01:01:02.895
Then came a signing deaf person

01:01:02.895 --> 01:01:04.702
and when he was about to die,

01:01:04.702 --> 01:01:06.620
he made his wish, and they granted it.

01:01:06.720 --> 01:01:10.211
When the burial was held, they brought the live interpreter

01:01:10.211 --> 01:01:13.120
in handcuffs and buried her with the deaf person.
